# Transition Consistency Rules

## System State: LOCKED ✓

### Critical Values (Do Not Modify Without Reason)
- Page transition duration: `1500ms`
- Page transition easing: `easeInOut`
- Loading bar visibility duration: `1500ms`
- Loading bar animation: `400ms easeOut`
- Blur exit state: `20px`
- Scale enter state: `0.98`
- Scale exit state: `1.05`

### Architecture
```
Layout wraps PageTransition wraps Page Content
LoadingBar rendered at layout level (above PageTransition)
AnimatePresence mode="wait" ensures clean sequencing
```

### Sync Requirement
LoadingBar and PageTransition durations MUST remain equal at 1500ms

### Component Files
- `/src/components/PageTransition.tsx` - Page animation wrapper
- `/src/components/LoadingBar.tsx` - Navigation indicator bar
- `/src/app/layout.tsx` - System integration point

### When Adding Features
1. Do not add animations during template transitions
2. Do not override transition duration with page-level animations
3. New pages automatically inherit transition system
4. Background effects (like NoiseOverlay) are outside transition wrapper

### Violations to Prevent
- ❌ Page-level competing animations
- ❌ Changing blur/scale without full system update
- ❌ Removing PageTransition wrapper
- ❌ Unsynchronized LoadingBar duration
- ❌ Adding AnimatePresence inside PageTransition

### Last Locked: May 16, 2026
